{
  "texts": [
    "This means that although first results are coherent and exciting, there is more work needed to control systematic biases and to be able to address the avalanche of data from all-sky surveys in the next decade.",
    "We are confident that this will happen and microlensing will achieve its full potential to deliver groundbreaking scientific results.",
    "Damien Hutsemékers and Lorraine Braibant discussions and material that helped shaping Fig. 23.",
    "acknowledges the support of the Swiss National Science Foundation under grant P500PT_203114.",
    "VM acknowledges partial support from Centro de Astrofísica de Valparaíso and ANID Fondecyt Regular 1231418."
  ]
}